				\begin{document}$${{\rm{h}}}_{{\rm{f}}}^{2}$$\end{document}hf2 = 0.5). This increased robustness towards dilution resulted in power above 40% in all cluster model scenarios with Nrep = 50 replicates within line and a genomic heritability of 50%. The level of genomic heritability (h2) was positively correlated with power (Fig. 4). However, at high \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
